# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# OnWay — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values before starting the server.
# Never commit .env to version control.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000

# ── Security ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generate with: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
JWT_SECRET=
SESSION_SECRET=

# ── Admin Panel Credentials ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
ADMIN_USERNAME=
ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Emergency recovery password for /admin/reset-password endpoint.
# Generate a strong random value. Leave empty to disable the endpoint.
MASTER_RECOVERY_PASSWORD=

# ── Domain / CORS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated list of allowed origins for CORS.
# Must match the exact protocol+domain+port your frontend is served from.
# Example: https://app.yourdomain.com,https://admin.yourdomain.com
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=

# ── Mobile App API URL ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This value is baked into the Expo/React Native bundle at build time.
# Set it BEFORE running: npm run expo:static:build
# Must be the full URL of your backend server (no trailing slash).
# Example: https://api.yourdomain.com
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=

# ── Firebase / Firestore ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Paste the full contents of your Firebase service account JSON as a single line.
# Download from: Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service accounts → Generate new private key
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT=

# ── Third-Party APIs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Google Maps API key (used for iOS/Android map rendering)
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# OTPIQ SMS gateway API key (https://otpiq.com)
OTP_IQ_API_KEY=

# ── Optional: Google OAuth for Admin Panel ────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed if you use Google sign-in for the admin panel.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
ADMIN_GOOGLE_EMAIL=

# ── Development Only ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to "true" ONLY in development to enable the 0000 test OTP bypass.
# Never set to "true" in production — NODE_ENV=production disables it regardless.
DEV_MODE=false
